{{Documentation subpage}} <!-- EDIT TEMPLATE DOCUMENTATION BELOW THIS LINE --> === Usage === This template can be used to mark articles or sections with old or out-of-date information.
To mark a section, use: : {{tlx|Update|type{{=}}section}} To add the date when the tag was added, use: : {{Tlx|Update|date{{=}}{{CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{CURRENTYEAR}}}}
This template will add articles to [[:Category:Wikipedia articles in need of updating]].
===Example=== <nowiki>{{update|documentation}}</nowiki> {{update|documentation}}
=== Alternatives === * If there is a dispute about the need for an update, an out-of-date article or section can be marked with {{tl|Out of date}}. * {{tl|Update after}} is an alternative for individual statements that will be out-of-date at a specifiable future date. It is a more recent and preferred alternative to [[Wikipedia:As of]]. It also adds articles to [[:Category:Wikipedia articles in need of updating]]. * See [[Wikipedia:Template_messages/Cleanup#Time-sensitive]] for alternatives unrelated to out-of-date information.
=== See also === * {{tl|Recentism}} * {{tl|Current}} * {{tl|Time-context}} * {{tl|As of?}} * {{tl|Updated}} * {{tl|As of}} * {{tl|Show by date}} * {{tl|Out of date}}
<includeonly> <!-- ADD CATEGORIES BELOW THIS LINE --> [[Category:Time and date maintenance templates|{{PAGENAME}}]] [[Category:Cleanup templates|{{PAGENAME}}]] [[Category:Temporal templates|{{PAGENAME}}]] [[Category:Templates needing talk links and other improvements|{{PAGENAME}}]]
